1. The method should return an integer representing the maximum amount of gold that can be collected.
2. The method should not modify the input grid.
3. The method should consider all possible paths to collect the maximum amount of gold.
4. The method should only visit cells with non-zero gold values.
5. The method should not visit the same cell more than once.
6. The method should be able to start and stop collecting gold from any position in the grid that has some gold.
